                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Unfortunately, this has started to cause some problems.
<br />

<br />
Pet classes are buffing up their pets, and don't want to lose them, so they're training all over the place.  I was in Gunthak helping a friend get gulf water for his Pure Blood quest and we saw people calling trains every couple of minutes, both to Dulak and to the PoK book.  People were getting really mad because you couldn't sit anywhere around the lighthouse, and people zoning into Gunthak from both Dulak and PoK/Stonebrunt were getting swarmed by trained mobs.
<br />

<br />
Even 65s with suspend are doing it, because you lose the pet if you zone with it suspended, and I guess they're too lazy to stop at the zone border and unsuspend before zoning.
<br />

<br />
Pet classes aren't invising, they're just getting SoW and training to get where they're going.  I hope this doesn't become a trend.    <img src="images/smiles/icon_neutral.gif" alt="icon_neutral.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Mistress Auli, Dark Elf Coercer of Vazaelle
<br />
Elder Binter, Vah Shir Prophet of Vazaelle</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
