                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Greetings,
<br />

<br />
   First thing I would like to remind everyone is that school is out for the summer, so yes, you will be getting a lot of the more immature players training again.  I wouldn't blame it all on the pet classes just yet.
<br />

<br />
   As for zoning suspended pets, this is about the only thing that I am unhappy about with this patch.  My main is a 65 Beastlord who often prefers to have a pet in storage and one for fighting.   When it was first announced that pet zoning was on test, I went and tested the system and feedbacked the lack of zoning suspended pets.
<br />

<br />
   I know many people would be willing to spend 5 - 10 AA for Suspend Minion 3, further I know it is not a technical challenge for them to implement it due to the way they changed pet storage with this patch.  Finally, with the buff changes they made to  pets with this patch, it really makes zero sense that the devs would be worried about people having a second pet suspended on zoning.  As such, I suspect the whole reason for this is simply that the devs didn't have time to get to it.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><ul><li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67241">Elder Kaatt</a>, Sixty-Five Year Old Khati Sha Feral Lord of Xev.<ul><li>BST65.250/Xv h++ 4(3.8)khp 4.1km ft5 r10 !G&gt;++++ e++ o T++ L++ H- f+ g b !t D+ X@</ul><li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362220">Aaeorm</a>, Coercion Technician of the Sixty-Fifth Tier of Xev.<ul><li>ENC65.2/Xv h-- 1.9(2.1)khp 4.3km ft1 r3 !G&gt;++++ e+&gt;++++ o T++ L-- H- f+ g b(@) c+&gt;++++ t-&gt;! D+ X@</ul></ul></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
